Rxvt-unicode, known as urxvt is fast and lightweight terminal emulator.

== Install ==
{{emerge|x11-terms/rxvt-unicode}}

== Font ==
One can set the font par application per se like the following.
{{file|~/.Xresources||<pre>
!-*-{ URxvt
!-*- General settings -*-
URxvt*termName:       rxvt-unicode-256color
URxvt*font:           xft:terminus:size=8:antialias=false
URxvt*allow_bold:     False
</pre>}}
Or else, set a font globaly for X applications.
{{file|~/.Xresources||<pre>
!-*-{ Global font
*font:                -*-terminus-*-*-*-*-*-*-*-*-*-*-*-*
!-*- Global Fore/background color -*-!
*background:          #101010
!-*-}
</pre>}}
Additionaly, one can tweak Xft settings.
{{file|~/.Xresources||<pre>
!-*-{ Xft settings
Xft*dpi:              96
Xft*antialias:        True
Xft*hinting:          Full
!-*-}
</pre>}}

== Scrollbar ==
{{file|~/.Xresources||<pre>
URxvt.scrollBar:          false
</pre>}}

== Copy/Paste and URL handling ==
A perl module can be used to get copy/paste and URL handling capabilities. Addidionally, you will need either {{Package|x11-misc/xsel}} or {{Package|x11-misc/xclip}} for copy/paste capabilities. One can grap the sources of a perl modules from muennich's [https://github.com/muennich/urxvt-perls github] or an [https://github.com/tokiclover/bar-overlay/tree/master/dev-perl/perl-URxvt ebuild] for example. Or either, get another perl module on the intertubes.

Here is an example of a `~/.Xressources'. The following lines can be added to `~/.Xdefaults' of course instead. The actual prefered location is the previous one.
{{file|~/.Xresources||<pre>
!-*- Perl extensions -*-
URxvt.perl-ext-common:default,clipboard,matcher,keyboard-select
URxvt.keysym.M-u:     perl:url-select:select_next
URxvt.urlLauncher:    /usr/bin/firefox
URxvt.underlineURLs:  True
URxvt.matcher.button: 1 
URxvt.keysym.M-Escape:perl:keyboard-select:activate
URxvt.keysym.M-c:     perl:clipboard:copy
URxvt.keysym.M-v:     perl:clipboard:paste
URxvt.keysym.M-C-v:   perl:clipboard:paste_escaped
!URxvt.copyCommand:   xsel -ib
!URxvt.pasteCommand:  xsel -ob
</pre>}}

== Icons ==
=== Menu icon ===
This adds menu entry and menu icon for urxvt.
If urxvt doesnt have a .desktop file, create one.
{{file|/usr/share/applications/urxvt.desktop||<pre>
[Desktop Entry]
Name=Urxvt
Comment=Terminal emulator
TryExec=urxvt
Exec=urxvt
Icon=terminal
Type=Application
Categories=GNOME;GTK;Utility;TerminalEmulator;System;
StartupNotify=true
</pre>}}

=== Application icon ===
For setting application icon urxvt has to be compiled with afterimage USE flag.
{{file|~/.Xresources||<pre>
URxvt.iconFile:    /usr/share/icons/hicolor/scalable/apps/Terminal.svg
</pre>}}

